"title": "7757: preaching, effects of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7757",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Faithful preaching leads to, through the grace of God, the repentance of sinners, the birth of faith and the nourishment of believers. It can also evoke hostility from unbelievers.</p>\n<h2>The basis of effective preaching</h2>\n<h3>It depends upon the grace of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:33\">ACT 4:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:10-Isa55:11\">ISA 55:10–55:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:26-Acts14:27\">ACT 14:26–14:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:10-1Cor15:11\">1CO 15:10–15:11</a></p>\n<h3>It depends upon the power of the cross, not human wisdom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:17-1Cor1:25\">1CO 1:17–1:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:1-1Cor2:5\">1CO 2:1–2:5</a></p>\n<h3>It depends upon the power of the Holy Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:18-Luke4:19\">LUK 4:18–4:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1-Isa61:2\">ISA 61:1–61:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:1-Acts2:11\">ACT 2:1–2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:44-Acts10:48\">ACT 10:44–10:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:4-1Cor2:5\">1CO 2:4–2:5</a></p>\n<h3>It requires effective, supporting prayer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:3-Col4:4\">COL 4:3–4:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:29-Acts4:31\">ACT 4:29–4:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:2-Acts6:4\">ACT 6:2–6:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:1-Acts13:5\">ACT 13:1–13:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:1\">2TH 3:1</a></p>\n<h3>It needs to be received with faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:2\">HEB 4:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:13\">1TH 2:13</a></p>\n<h2>Preaching and the repentance of sinners</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:41\">MAT 12:41</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:32\">LUK 11:32</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:1-Jonah3:10\">JON 3:1–3:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:1-Matt3:6\">MAT 3:1–3:6</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:3-Mark1:5\">MRK 1:3–1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:3-Luke3:6\">LUK 3:3–3:6</a></p>\n<h2>Preaching and the birth of faith</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:4\">ACT 4:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:38-Acts2:41\">ACT 2:38–2:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:9-Acts8:13\">ACT 8:9–8:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:11-Acts17:12\">ACT 17:11–17:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:1-1Cor15:2\">1CO 15:1–15:2</a></p>\n<h2>Preaching and the nourishment of believers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:21-Acts14:22\">ACT 14:21–14:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:25-Rom16:27\">ROM 16:25–16:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11-Eph4:16\">EPH 4:11–4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:6-Col2:7\">COL 2:6–2:7</a></p>\n<h2>Effective preaching and its authentication by miracles</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:20\">MRK 16:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:23-Matt4:25\">MAT 4:23–4:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:1-Luke9:6\">LUK 9:1–9:6</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:5-Matt10:14\">MAT 10:5–10:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:7-Mark6:11\">MRK 6:7–6:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:29-Acts4:30\">ACT 4:29–4:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:5-Acts8:8\">ACT 8:5–8:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:1-Acts14:3\">ACT 14:1–14:3</a></p>\n<h2>Inappropriate responses to preaching</h2>\n<h3>Amazement</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:28-Matt7:29\">MAT 7:28–7:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:31-Luke4:32\">LUK 4:31–4:32</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:21-Mark1:22\">MRK 1:21–1:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:5-Acts2:12\">ACT 2:5–2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:13-Acts4:14\">ACT 4:13–4:14</a></p>\n<h3>Offence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:1-Mark6:6\">MRK 6:1–6:6</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:54-Matt13:58\">MAT 13:54–13:58</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:22-1Cor1:23\">1CO 1:22–1:23</a></p>\n<h3>Mere academic interest</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:16-Acts17:32\">ACT 17:16–17:32</a> <em>Paul in Athens and before the Areopagus</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:22-Acts24:26\">ACT 24:22–24:26</a> <em>Paul before Felix and Drusilla</em></p>\n<h3>Mockery</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:32\">ACT 17:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:15-2Chr36:16\">2CH 36:15–36:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:13\">ACT 2:13</a></p>\n<h3>Hostility</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:13\">ACT 17:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:1-Acts4:3\">ACT 4:1–4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:27-Acts5:40\">ACT 5:27–5:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:54-Acts7:60\">ACT 7:54–7:60</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:49-Acts13:51\">ACT 13:49–13:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:5-Acts17:9\">ACT 17:5–17:9</a></p>",
